  Eze Israel Kanu, father of the leader of the Indigenous People of Biafra, Nnamdi Kanu, has died, a report by PUNCH said. This comes four months after his mother, Ugoeze Sally Kanu, passed away. Eze Kanu was the traditional ruler of Afara Ukwu Umuahia community till his death. The traditional council of his community led by Edward Ibeabuchi confirmed his demise. Eze Kanu had not been seen in the public since September 2017, after a detachment of soldiers raided his palace. One of his sons, Emmanuel, also confirmed the demise of his father.